## рџ”№ 2. Why Virtual Environment is needed

In real projects:

* Different projects use different versions
* Different libraries required
* Cannot install globally

So we create:

```
virtual environment (venv)
```

It keeps project isolated.

Real automation always uses venv.

---

## рџ”№ 3. Create Project Folder

Create folder:

```
HPM_API_AUTOMATION
```

Inside open terminal.

Example:

```bash
mkdir HPM_API_AUTOMATION
cd HPM_API_AUTOMATION
```

This will be your framework root.

---

## рџ”№ 4. Create Virtual Environment

Run:

```bash
python -m venv venv
```

Folder created:

```
venv/
```

Activate venv.

Windows:

```bash
venv\Scripts\activate
```

Linux / Mac:

```bash
source venv/bin/activate
```

After activation:

```
(venv) C:\HPM_API_AUTOMATION>
```

This means correct.

---

## рџ”№ 5. Install Required Libraries

Install pytest:

```bash
pip install pytest
```

Install requests:

```bash
pip install requests
```

Install playwright (later used for UI / API mix):

```bash
pip install playwright
```

Optional but common:

```bash
pip install faker
pip install python-dotenv
pip install pytest-html
```

Real projects use these.

---

## рџ”№ 6. Create requirements.txt

Save installed packages.

Run:

```bash
pip freeze > requirements.txt
```

File created:

```
requirements.txt
```

Used in real projects for CI/CD.

Example inside:

```
pytest
requests
playwright
faker
```

